==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Parfocal
<hw>Par*fo"cal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Pari-</ets> +
<ets>focal</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Opt.)</fld> <def>With the lower focal
points all in the same plane; -- said of sets of eyepieces so mounted
that they may be interchanged without varying the focus of the
instrument (as a microscope or telescope) with which they are
used.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧the convenience of a microscope with
<xex>parfocal</xex> objective lenses⟦rdquo⟧⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

